headline.seo: ‘Bodega Clinicas’ Draw Interest of Health Officials
headline.main: As ‘Bodega Clinicas’ Fill Void, Health Officials Are Torn
headline.print_headline: As ‘Bodega Clinicas’ Fill Void, Health Officials Are Torn

docs.abstract: Storefront doctors' offices known as 'bodega clinicas' that line streets of immigrant neighborhoods In Los Angeles are servicing mostly uninsured Latinos, leaving county health officials to examine clinics’ place in nation’s health system; health care experts say they have little understanding of who owns and operates them, how they are regulated and what quality of medical care they provide.
